1
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:59,130
MY DEAREST NEMEZIS

2
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:06,590
What is the name of that restaurant?

3
00:01:06,890 --> 00:01:08,330
Maybe I know her.

4
00:01:09,030 --> 00:01:10,170
Probably not.

5
00:01:10,970 --> 00:01:12,310
It is located in a remote area.

6
00:01:12,410 --> 00:01:13,810
Maybe that's why he doesn't have customers.

7
00:01:13,910 --> 00:01:14,930
But the food is good.

8
00:01:15,030 --> 00:01:16,160
Are you sure?

9
00:01:16,860 --> 00:01:18,550
I have very high standards.

10
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:21,510
So eat at home. I'll go alone.

11
00:01:23,930 --> 00:01:24,910
I'll try it.

12
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,040
I can do it myself.

13
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:55,700
How hard did you try to defeat me?

14
00:01:57,220 --> 00:01:59,220
I can ask you the same thing.

15
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:06,360
Done.

16
00:02:21,210 --> 00:02:22,490
Oh my God. No...

17
00:02:22,690 --> 00:02:23,720
Quick, quick.

18
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:34,910
- Ha Jin, I'm in front of... - Don't come here.

19
00:02:36,330 --> 00:02:37,960
- What? - Don't come here.

20
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,690
There is a Black Dragon.

21
00:03:03,310 --> 00:03:04,280
What are you doing?

22
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:05,480
No...

23
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,530
In that restaurant there is...

24
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:09,220
Black...

25
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:10,540
Black?

26
00:03:12,810 --> 00:03:13,980
A dark past.

27
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:16,400
The one who cheated on me during a video game.

28
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,530
He created the darkest past of my life.

29
00:03:18,730 --> 00:03:20,420
I can't meet him alone.

30
00:03:20,620 --> 00:03:22,050
Is that why you ran away?

31
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:24,510
You are acting like a fraud.

32
00:03:24,610 --> 00:03:26,070
Use this to teach him a lesson.

33
00:03:26,170 --> 00:03:26,830
Let's go.

34
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:29,160
I can't. My first love...

35
00:03:33,670 --> 00:03:35,310
It's my first love.

36
00:03:35,410 --> 00:03:37,040
He's not a fraud.

37
00:03:37,140 --> 00:03:38,610
I never want to see him again.

38
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:40,020
I wouldn't like to see him.

39
00:03:41,810 --> 00:03:42,560
I also understand,

40
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,340
How does it feel?

41
00:03:45,090 --> 00:03:48,250
but this attitude is a bit...

42
00:03:52,820 --> 00:03:53,790
Sorry.

43
00:03:54,190 --> 00:03:55,670
I didn't want to do it.

44
00:03:57,220 --> 00:03:58,370
I thought it was a wall.

45
00:03:58,470 --> 00:03:59,720
Why do you have such a strong...

46
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:01,100
chest?

47
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,920
Did you exercise instead of working?

48
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:05,430
Of course I do both.

49
00:04:06,330 --> 00:04:08,690
Keep comparing me to the wall.

50
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:11,650
- That's enough. - Enough?

51
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:13,320
That word is not in my dictionary.

52
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:16,660
Will you continue to hide?

53
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:18,920
What if I went there and ran into him?

54
00:04:19,020 --> 00:04:21,150
- What does he look like? - Excuse me?

55
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:23,520
I need to know so we can avoid it.

56
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,080
I don't know.

57
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,790
I saw him briefly when he was little.

58
00:04:27,990 --> 00:04:29,900
His face must have changed quite a bit.

59
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,060
So you might not recognize him.

60
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,430
You are right.

61
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:41,580
Someone was passing by earlier.

62
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:42,700
Did he leave?

63
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:47,580
Black Dragon is Su Jeongin's director?

64
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,060
Oh my God.

65
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:53,620
God.

66
00:04:54,620 --> 00:04:56,100
PART 5

67
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:58,440
I can take the bus from here.

68
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:00,600
I'm going now.

69
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:27,940
I thought you were going to the office.

70
00:05:28,340 --> 00:05:29,680
Which bus are you taking?

71
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:33,180
Number 770.

72
00:05:34,450 --> 00:05:35,440
Will you wait with me?

73
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,690
He will definitely be here soon.

74
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,760
I won it at the arcade.

75
00:06:06,860 --> 00:06:08,330
I know you like this character.

76
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,890
What? Is this too touching?

77
00:06:22,790 --> 00:06:25,820
I guess so. Who else would give you a gift like me?

78
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:27,990
You don't have to be so grateful.

79
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:36,850
That's not true.

80
00:06:39,310 --> 00:06:40,760
Can't you tell?

81
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:43,570
It is obviously fake.

82
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:45,500
People don't understand that.

83
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:48,320
It's not just a character. It's Toggaengyi.

84
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:49,480
Toggaengyi. Toggaengyi.

85
00:06:49,580 --> 00:06:51,390
It is obvious that he has a name.

86
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,050
Don't bother if you don't like it.

87
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:56,670
I'll accept it out of politeness.

88
00:07:18,790 --> 00:07:21,280
Arrive home safely.

89
00:07:23,580 --> 00:07:24,830
Okay. I'll go.

90
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:58,050
YONGSUNG DEPARTMENT HOUSE

91
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:04,170
YONGSUNG FOOD DEPARTMENT

92
00:08:04,170 --> 00:08:06,460
Apparently yesterday's meeting was quite heated.

93
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:08,590
I heard you were the only survivor.

94
00:08:08,690 --> 00:08:09,600
Is that true?

95
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:11,320
Maybe so...

96
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,520
- Hello. - Hello.

97
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:30,810
Catering Department

98
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:32,920
focuses on edibles, as you can see.

99
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:35,930
They are said to lack diversity and accessibility.

100
00:08:36,130 --> 00:08:37,840
We need popular brands from social networks,

101
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:40,570
to attract new customers.

102
00:08:40,670 --> 00:08:42,250
They can't just be popular.

103
00:08:42,650 --> 00:08:45,650
They must not match our competitors.

104
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:47,860
I created this list of companies.

105
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:50,730
YONGSUNG DEPARTMENT HOUSE, FOOD DEPARTMENT ENTERPRISES

106
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,100
Excellent.

107
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,590
We can continue.

108
00:08:56,690 --> 00:08:57,430
Okay.

109
00:08:58,540 --> 00:09:00,520
Food separation is important

110
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:01,980
for customers and our profit.

111
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,850
It is the pinnacle of the restoration project.

112
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:05,340
Make it matter.

113
00:09:05,740 --> 00:09:08,800
Here you can prove your skills.

114
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:10,820
Don't let me down this time.

115
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:25,520
It was such a challenging morning.

116
00:09:27,020 --> 00:09:27,830
Not

117
00:09:28,730 --> 00:09:31,520
Why did the donkey suddenly come to the restaurant?

118
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,620
- The thing is... - You said you weren't seeing him.

119
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:35,590
and that you only talk to him once in a while.

120
00:09:35,690 --> 00:09:38,060
It's true, but suddenly he appeared.

121
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:40,900
God, I don't even know what to do.

122
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,430
What should I do?

123
00:09:42,530 --> 00:09:44,460
I also didn't know what to do.

124
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:47,260
I brought the director there, but we couldn't eat.

125
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,320
I know.

126
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,510
When did you become close to him?

127
00:09:50,610 --> 00:09:51,860
You said he was crazy.

128
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,180
Probably not anymore.

129
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:56,250
Actually

130
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:58,160
he's not that bad,

131
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:01,370
when I met him.

132
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:03,250
He's not that bad?

133
00:10:05,450 --> 00:10:06,550
Listen.

134
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:09,500
Let's say from the Black Dragon

135
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:15,030
became a decent person like the director.

136
00:10:15,130 --> 00:10:16,260
What would you think?

137
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:18,230
What? They have nothing in common.

138
00:10:18,330 --> 00:10:20,100
- But what if? - I know.

139
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,900
How could he become a decent person?

140
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,390
He was never good.

141
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:24,840
Even if he won the Nobel Prize,

142
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:27,270
To me he is still a fraud. Nothing has changed.

143
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:29,040
Don't you want to change jobs?

144
00:10:29,540 --> 00:10:31,020
Why do you keep changing the subject?

145
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,980
Because you want him to go to the restaurant?

146
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,970
I didn't force him to come.

147
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:36,300
So who did it?

148
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:37,710
What?

149
00:10:39,460 --> 00:10:40,390
That's strange.

150
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:42,210
Why won't you answer me?

151
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:47,950
Yes, director.

152
00:10:48,450 --> 00:10:50,610
Haven't changed your password yet?

153
00:10:51,410 --> 00:10:53,540
I told you to change it quickly.

154
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:55,130
Okay, I understand.

155
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:59,010
Something urgent has come up at work. I have to go.

156
00:10:59,110 --> 00:11:01,170
We'll talk later, okay?

157
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,080
Why is he in such a hurry?

158
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:12,890
YONGSUNG

159
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:16,410
I left my purse at the reception.

160
00:11:32,540 --> 00:11:36,330
Wait for me, Director. Please?

161
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,320
- Are you close? - Ha Jin.

162
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:42,270
What are you doing here?

163
00:11:49,820 --> 00:11:51,120
I am at work.

164
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:53,500
Did you come to see me?

165
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:55,850
Answer me. Are you close?

166
00:11:55,950 --> 00:11:57,880
Excuse me? Yes.

167
00:11:57,980 --> 00:11:58,730
How close?

168
00:11:59,130 --> 00:12:00,320
Very close.

169
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:01,960
Do you also know about his first love?

170
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:04,520
Of course I know.

171
00:12:05,020 --> 00:12:06,720
For Ju Yeon, his first love was

172
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,680
a disgusting curse.

173
00:12:10,780 --> 00:12:11,980
And it still is.

174
00:12:13,130 --> 00:12:15,820
I know you want to play, Ju Yeon.

175
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:17,990
Do grades only matter?

176
00:12:18,090 --> 00:12:19,760
On a day like this, you should get rid of stress,

177
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:21,400
to maintain good grades.

178
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:22,940
Let's play.

179
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:25,030
What are we going to play? Cards?

180
00:12:25,130 --> 00:12:26,150
League? Star?

181
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:30,510
I want to play this.

182
00:12:35,190 --> 00:12:36,650
THE LEGEND OF FEVER

183
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:39,600
BLACK DRAGON

184
00:12:41,580 --> 00:12:43,900
Wow, you came to me.

185
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,450
You are the best, Bbanjju.

186
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:50,500
Do you have what I asked for?

187
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:54,360
Fried chicken? Plain or spicy?

188
00:12:54,460 --> 00:12:56,550
- Thank you. Here you go. - Wow.

189
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:57,680
Let's go. Let's go.

190
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:05,090
Really, Sin Won...

191
00:13:05,490 --> 00:13:06,050
Yes?

192
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:08,950
I confess...

193
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:11,510
my love for Strawberry.

194
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:14,080
Amazing.

195
00:13:16,550 --> 00:13:17,690
How are you going to tell her?

196
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:21,160
How did you do it?

197
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:25,930
They always professed their love for me. I never did.

198
00:13:26,530 --> 00:13:27,930
Do it casually.

199
00:13:28,030 --> 00:13:30,250
Sincerity is more important than method.

200
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:33,850
And you are the good-looking heir to Yongsung.

201
00:13:33,950 --> 00:13:35,420
Who would reject you?

202
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:36,460
God.

203
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,360
God, you are so superficial.

204
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:40,500
Strawberry doesn't know who I am.

205
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:43,970
She likes me the way I am.

206
00:13:45,460 --> 00:13:49,070
You have to tell me when you start dating.

207
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:51,900
If you date for 22 days, I'll give you 200 won.

208
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,470
22 days?

209
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,630
This is a collect call.

210
00:14:11,730 --> 00:14:13,060
Please verify the caller.

211
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,370
This is Sin Won, Bbanjju. Don't fold. Don't fold.

212
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:17,720
- What is it? - What do you mean?

213
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:19,620
You haven't called me in a long time.

214
00:14:20,020 --> 00:14:20,890
You forgot

215
00:14:21,290 --> 00:14:22,930
on me because you are busy

216
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:24,180
dating Strawberry?

217
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:25,880
Never again...

218
00:14:26,980 --> 00:14:27,670
What?

219
00:14:28,370 --> 00:14:29,900
Never say that name again.

220
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,740
What? Why?

221
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,580
Did you get kicked out?

222
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:37,630
But why? You're not missing anything.

223
00:14:37,730 --> 00:14:38,720
What's the problem?

224
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:40,180
Moist existence.

225
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,850
She is disgusted by my existence.

226
00:14:43,650 --> 00:14:46,370
How could she be so cruel?

227
00:14:46,670 --> 00:14:48,140
You shouldn't call me either.

228
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,810
I won't do anything stupid again.

229
00:14:51,710 --> 00:14:54,140
Hey, hey, Bbanjju. Don't fold. Don't do it.

230
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:57,860
That's probably when it started.

231
00:14:59,430 --> 00:15:01,790
He only briefly acted his age,

232
00:15:02,190 --> 00:15:03,760
because he started to focus only on

233
00:15:03,860 --> 00:15:05,820
to become the perfect successor.

234
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:08,590
Successor?

235
00:15:08,690 --> 00:15:11,220
I'm glad he wasn't an alien or a brawler.

236
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,010
Excuse me?

237
00:15:12,810 --> 00:15:13,740
Easy

238
00:15:14,340 --> 00:15:17,020
That's how much his first love hurt him.

239
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,830
Why did he lie about his age?

240
00:15:18,930 --> 00:15:21,080
I was shocked when I saw him at the meeting.

241
00:15:21,180 --> 00:15:23,400
I know he lied about his age,

242
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,150
but his existence is disgusting?

243
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:26,660
That was cruel.

244
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,640
It would hurt me too.

245
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:31,090
She was upset, okay?

246
00:15:31,190 --> 00:15:33,190
What she did was still wrong.

247
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:36,360
God.

248
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:40,410
Who is the bad person, really?

249
00:15:41,210 --> 00:15:42,450
Do you think it's Ju Yeon?

250
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:43,930
So Su Jeong?

251
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:47,450
It doesn't matter.

252
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:49,610
They won't meet again anyway.

253
00:15:50,210 --> 00:15:52,280
Of course, if they met,

254
00:15:52,580 --> 00:15:55,080
He certainly wouldn't forgive anyone,

255
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:57,040
who ruined his life.

256
00:15:57,540 --> 00:16:00,910
He will try to destroy her future at all costs.

257
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:04,060
First, he will not be able to live in this country.

258
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:04,690
NO.

259
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,580
Will he fire her from the company first?

260
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:11,230
He is ruthless and terrifying.

261
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:13,540
She can't do it.

262
00:16:15,230 --> 00:16:16,730
Why are you so shocked?

263
00:16:18,970 --> 00:16:20,120
Was it too scary?

264
00:16:20,220 --> 00:16:21,970
Su Jeong is the scary one.

265
00:16:22,070 --> 00:16:23,900
From what I understand,

266
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:27,090
will try to avenge him for the shame and humiliation.

267
00:16:27,190 --> 00:16:28,830
Her life motto is:

268
00:16:28,930 --> 00:16:30,470
"An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth."

269
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:33,770
Will Su Jeong have to leave the country?

270
00:16:33,870 --> 00:16:37,800
Ju Yeon will have to leave the planet.

271
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:39,220
If that's the case,

272
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:42,210
you mean,

273
00:16:42,610 --> 00:16:46,400
that Su Jeong is just as passionate as Ju Yeon?

274
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:48,160
If I know her well,

275
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:50,030
so yes.

276
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:55,700
I'm glad they'll never see each other.

277
00:16:55,810 --> 00:16:57,310
What if they see each other?

278
00:16:58,110 --> 00:16:58,710
Excuse me?

279
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:00,860
What if they see each other every day?

280
00:17:43,090 --> 00:17:43,830
No...

281
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:03,760
Wait, were you talking about Team Leader Baek?

282
00:18:03,860 --> 00:18:04,780
The CEO killer?

283
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:07,650
Why are they so calm?

284
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:11,630
- That's not possible... - Yes.

285
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:13,930
They didn't recognize each other.

286
00:18:14,430 --> 00:18:16,940
Wow. I'm relieved.

287
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:19,680
It happened a long time ago.

288
00:18:19,780 --> 00:18:20,960
And they only saw each other briefly.

289
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:22,330
It's too early for relief.

290
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:26,000
They became friends and there is something between them.

291
00:18:26,110 --> 00:18:27,320
What if they get even closer?

292
00:18:27,420 --> 00:18:29,400
and they fall in love?

293
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,690
And if they later find out the truth...

294
00:18:33,570 --> 00:18:37,230
YONGSUNG'S SUCCESSOR IS CRITICIZED FOR UNFAIR DISMISSAL

295
00:18:37,330 --> 00:18:39,860
EMPLOYEE PLANTED A BOMB IN A YONGSUNG DEPARTMENT

296
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,240
- Horror! - Horror!

297
00:18:42,340 --> 00:18:43,800
We have to divide them.

298
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:45,830
They must never find out that they know each other. Never.

299
00:18:45,930 --> 00:18:46,800
Yes.

300
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:11,880
What are you doing?

301
00:19:11,980 --> 00:19:13,720
What? We have to go up quickly.

302
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:15,410
You can't waste a second.

303
00:19:20,220 --> 00:19:22,370
Really, do you know Miss Baek?

304
00:19:22,470 --> 00:19:23,950
I checked it even better.

305
00:19:24,050 --> 00:19:25,640
Why are you doing something so pointless?

306
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,590
I said you can stop.

307
00:19:28,190 --> 00:19:30,720
It occurred to me that I wasn't thorough enough.

308
00:19:30,820 --> 00:19:32,160
So I checked it out more.

309
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:35,640
She seems more stubborn and passionate than I thought.

310
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:37,470
Wouldn't it be difficult to work with her?

311
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:39,750
That's why you said she would be a good fit for me.

312
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:42,600
Another problem occurred.

313
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:45,730
He seems interested in someone at work.

314
00:19:47,580 --> 00:19:48,960
Is he interested in anyone?

315
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:51,060
Apparently yes.

316
00:19:51,660 --> 00:19:53,800
I know you despise office romances.

317
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:57,190
You warned me not to date anyone from work.

318
00:19:57,290 --> 00:19:59,790
I'm asking if it would be okay.

319
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,530
I'm not sure.

320
00:20:16,890 --> 00:20:18,820
Is he interested in anyone?

321
00:20:22,170 --> 00:20:24,990
Could it be me?

322
00:20:27,180 --> 00:20:28,450
It won't be good.

323
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:38,990
GRACE

324
00:20:53,260 --> 00:20:54,140
Ha Jin.

325
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,830
You're here. Where do you want to sit?

326
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:07,610
Su Jeong.

327
00:21:09,340 --> 00:21:10,930
A PERFECT PLACE FOR A DATE!

328
00:21:10,930 --> 00:21:12,910
MEN GET FREE FOOD AND DRINK.

329
00:21:21,550 --> 00:21:23,810
God, it seems you can't sit here.

330
00:21:23,910 --> 00:21:25,460
If someone comes, I'll assert myself.

331
00:21:27,470 --> 00:21:29,560
What did you want to tell me?

332
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:34,640
You're not introducing me to those men, are you?

333
00:21:36,770 --> 00:21:38,000
NO.

334
00:21:46,730 --> 00:21:48,040
What are you doing after work today?

335
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:49,550
You're going straight home, right?

336
00:21:50,050 --> 00:21:52,330
Don't work overtime. If you have to, work alone.

337
00:21:52,430 --> 00:21:53,890
Be alone during overtime.

338
00:21:54,490 --> 00:21:55,510
What's his problem?

339
00:21:56,210 --> 00:21:58,190
Is he bored because he has no customers?

340
00:21:58,690 --> 00:22:00,110
I thought it wasn't that bad.

341
00:22:02,090 --> 00:22:03,970
I printed out the logo routing.

342
00:22:05,850 --> 00:22:08,120
Wow, I like it.

343
00:22:08,220 --> 00:22:10,800
This is exactly how we imagined it.

344
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,180
Yes, I know.

345
00:22:12,380 --> 00:22:14,350
It's the first round, but it's pretty good.

346
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:15,940
We don't need to change it too much.

347
00:22:16,340 --> 00:22:17,250
Wow...

348
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:22,680
Manager Kim is truly the best.

349
00:22:23,180 --> 00:22:25,360
How come he's always perfect?

350
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:27,130
I can't believe it.

351
00:22:29,060 --> 00:22:29,860
On On?

352
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:34,290
You are also about to join his fan club.

353
00:22:34,590 --> 00:22:36,180
- Fan club? - I mean,

354
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:39,100
that there is a fan club for leader Kim at work.

355
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:42,280
I think it's led by Miss Jeong from the design team.

356
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:44,300
Is he that popular?

357
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:45,750
Yes.

358
00:22:46,250 --> 00:22:48,860
You know, he's really amazing.

359
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:51,170
He is kind, he smiles often,

360
00:22:51,270 --> 00:22:53,220
he is friendly and polite.

361
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:56,430
How do you know that? You've never worked with him.

362
00:22:57,430 --> 00:22:59,690
We had coffee once.

363
00:23:00,090 --> 00:23:02,190
He wanted to ask me something.

364
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:03,210
Just the two of you?

365
00:23:03,510 --> 00:23:05,720
That's too obvious a step.

366
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:07,720
He could have asked me instead.

367
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:09,370
He's gone crazy. You're much younger.

368
00:23:09,470 --> 00:23:11,580
No, it was nothing like that.

369
00:23:12,380 --> 00:23:13,790
What did he ask you?

370
00:23:14,390 --> 00:23:15,430
Ide o to,

371
00:23:16,730 --> 00:23:19,690
that he asked me about you, team leader.

372
00:23:21,190 --> 00:23:23,020
- At me? - Yes.

373
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:38,640
Team Leader Baek Su Jeong,

374
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:41,580
a good opportunity arose somewhere else.

375
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:43,780
Are you interested in a job change?

376
00:24:09,550 --> 00:24:11,200
I got scared.

377
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:13,360
Just work.

378
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:16,040
I'm going crazy...

379
00:24:17,670 --> 00:24:19,330
Do you have time, Manager Kim?

380
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:24,760
YONGSUNG DEPARTMENT HOUSE

381
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:26,160
Yes.

382
00:24:29,250 --> 00:24:30,580
Where is Team Leader Baek...

383
00:24:30,980 --> 00:24:32,640
She left early.

384
00:24:35,950 --> 00:24:37,670
- Good night. - Good night.

385
00:24:38,470 --> 00:24:41,440
Maybe Team Leader Baek was also interested in the leader.

386
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:43,200
That's not possible.

387
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:46,030
So why would he meet her after work?

388
00:24:51,070 --> 00:24:52,140
What did you say?

389
00:24:54,170 --> 00:24:55,520
Which part?

390
00:24:55,620 --> 00:24:57,130
Who is Team Leader Baek interested in...

391
00:24:58,030 --> 00:24:59,370
Who is he meeting with?

392
00:25:00,370 --> 00:25:03,220
With leader Kim Sin Won from the design team.

393
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:08,120
Representative Yang Jun Su!

394
00:25:09,790 --> 00:25:10,570
Yes.

395
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:13,860
You have the top button undone.

396
00:25:14,060 --> 00:25:17,090
Please straighten up and dress properly.

397
00:25:23,750 --> 00:25:24,510
Thank you.

398
00:25:25,410 --> 00:25:26,780
- Thank you! - Thank you.

399
00:25:37,230 --> 00:25:39,020
We could talk in the office.

400
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,630
Why did you invite me to the cafe?

401
00:25:40,730 --> 00:25:41,820
That's a waste of time.

402
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:44,100
Ide o to,

403
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:47,470
that I don't know where to start.

404
00:25:48,570 --> 00:25:50,560
Do you mind if I start?

405
00:25:50,660 --> 00:25:52,850
Of course not. Go ahead.

406
00:25:53,650 --> 00:25:54,850
Leader Kim,

407
00:25:55,950 --> 00:25:58,110
Are you interested in me?

408
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:02,220
Yes.

409
00:26:02,820 --> 00:26:05,590
I will not allow my employee to become a victim of gossip.

410
00:26:06,290 --> 00:26:08,310
That's why I'm going there. That's the reason.

411
00:26:26,630 --> 00:26:27,250
He wasn't...

412
00:26:30,410 --> 00:26:31,240
It's me.

413
00:26:40,610 --> 00:26:41,680
I'm asking you.

414
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:43,580
Are you interested in me?

415
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:50,850
I would be lying,

416
00:26:51,950 --> 00:26:53,030
if I said no.

417
00:26:54,550 --> 00:26:57,280
But I'm not interested in you in a romantic way.

418
00:26:57,380 --> 00:26:59,050
What are you saying? Of course not.

419
00:26:59,450 --> 00:27:00,940
You're not angry with me,

420
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:02,650
because you were friends with the former director?

421
00:27:03,050 --> 00:27:06,720
Was it the one before? Or the one before that?

422
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:08,750
- Excuse me? - If not,

423
00:27:08,850 --> 00:27:10,850
Why are you asking about me?

424
00:27:11,950 --> 00:27:14,870
I think you're wrong...

425
00:27:14,970 --> 00:27:15,950
No excuses.

426
00:27:16,450 --> 00:27:18,220
Don't tell behind my back.

427
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:20,110
If you have a complaint, talk to me.

428
00:27:20,210 --> 00:27:21,470
Instead of diving.

429
00:27:21,570 --> 00:27:22,810
I'll go.

430
00:27:23,210 --> 00:27:24,730
Wait. I have to tell you something.

431
00:27:24,830 --> 00:27:25,800
What is it about?

432
00:27:25,900 --> 00:27:27,110
Ide o to...

433
00:27:27,910 --> 00:27:30,850
Will you continue to work for Director Ban?

434
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:32,850
Why do you ask that?

435
00:27:33,350 --> 00:27:34,530
Are you going to fire me?

436
00:27:34,630 --> 00:27:36,620
No, not at all.

437
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:40,000
What I mean is...

438
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:42,480
What did I want to say?

439
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:46,190
Goodbye.

440
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:54,800
KISSES FOR 6,000 WON

441
00:27:55,350 --> 00:27:57,140
BAEK SU JEONG A KIM SIN WON

442
00:28:07,870 --> 00:28:08,630
NO.

443
00:28:09,630 --> 00:28:11,580
He must have better taste.

444
00:28:14,490 --> 00:28:16,680
I ALSO HAVE AN IDEAL TYPE.

445
00:28:19,090 --> 00:28:21,860
I APPRECIATE THAT OPINION. DO YOU MIND IF I LEAVE?

446
00:28:30,430 --> 00:28:31,140
NO!

447
00:28:43,060 --> 00:28:44,700
Who is this late?

448
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:46,400
Don't get up, Dad.

449
00:28:55,020 --> 00:28:57,460
I'm not going to sign another contract, am I?

450
00:28:57,960 --> 00:28:59,870
That's not true.

451
00:29:01,620 --> 00:29:02,590
Eat first.

452
00:29:02,890 --> 00:29:04,920
The eggs look very tasty today.

453
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:06,350
I haven't had dinner yet.

454
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:12,620
I'm here to give you some important advice.

455
00:29:15,310 --> 00:29:16,160
Me?

456
00:29:16,460 --> 00:29:18,780
It is important to separate work and life.

457
00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:21,910
But the boss shouldn't stand by and watch,

458
00:29:22,310 --> 00:29:24,270
how his employee's life is being ruined.

459
00:29:26,450 --> 00:29:27,100
Excuse me?

460
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:32,100
Read it.

461
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:37,350
Did you come to recommend a comic to me?

462
00:29:37,750 --> 00:29:38,930
KISSES FOR 6,000 WON

463
00:29:39,030 --> 00:29:41,740
I know you have no one to talk to about this...

464
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:44,140
Right here. Read this section.

465
00:29:44,140 --> 00:29:46,990
It explains why you shouldn't fall for a womanizer.

466
00:29:47,090 --> 00:29:49,040
You also said that your first love cheated on you.

467
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:51,020
You can't become a victim of a womanizer either.

468
00:29:52,850 --> 00:29:54,200
What are you talking about all of a sudden...

469
00:29:54,300 --> 00:29:57,920
I know you're interested in Leader Kim.

470
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:00,530
And?

471
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:04,240
- Don't you? - No.

472
00:30:05,810 --> 00:30:09,230
Why did you meet him at the cafe after work?

473
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:12,230
How do you know that?

474
00:30:13,890 --> 00:30:16,470
I happened to see you when I was walking by.

475
00:30:17,070 --> 00:30:18,030
I am disappointed.

476
00:30:18,630 --> 00:30:21,460
I didn't think you would succumb to his charm too.

477
00:30:23,850 --> 00:30:25,040
He smiles a lot,

478
00:30:25,340 --> 00:30:27,400
He is friendly and polite. Such charm?

479
00:30:29,620 --> 00:30:31,050
You too...

480
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:34,190
Do you like things like that?

481
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:37,230
No, I don't.

482
00:30:38,630 --> 00:30:40,220
A man should only be like that with me,

483
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:41,850
even if he was a little clumsy.

484
00:30:45,390 --> 00:30:48,060
I have to agree. Love is sacred.

485
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:50,540
So you're not interested in Manager Kim...

486
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:52,370
I said I'm not interested.

487
00:30:52,770 --> 00:30:55,400
I asked him why he was asking others about me.

488
00:30:56,300 --> 00:30:57,180
Is he asking questions?

489
00:30:57,780 --> 00:30:59,830
I think he's trying to find my weakness.

490
00:31:26,260 --> 00:31:27,430
Delicious. Teda...

491
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,220
It's delicious.

492
00:31:32,220 --> 00:31:32,950
Amazing.

493
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:36,220
Let's eat.

494
00:31:53,470 --> 00:31:55,960
I'll definitely have fun.

495
00:31:56,060 --> 00:31:57,990
Although I won't be fooled by womanizers.

496
00:31:58,490 --> 00:31:59,980
Sorry to bother you so late.

497
00:32:00,180 --> 00:32:02,080
Tell your father I'm sorry.

498
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:03,660
Okay.

499
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,070
Really,

500
00:32:08,870 --> 00:32:11,930
if I were really interested in Leader Kim,

501
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:13,310
What would you do?

502
00:32:13,510 --> 00:32:15,620
What if I didn't care that he was a womanizer?

503
00:32:16,120 --> 00:32:17,350
I would prevent you from doing that.

504
00:32:17,450 --> 00:32:19,350
until you lose interest in him.

505
00:32:21,770 --> 00:32:22,540
Why?

506
00:32:23,740 --> 00:32:26,220
Is this your duty as a boss?

507
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:27,530
Easy...

508
00:32:29,230 --> 00:32:30,300
I don't like it.

509
00:32:43,810 --> 00:32:44,770
I'm going now.

510
00:33:01,010 --> 00:33:01,760
Sister.

511
00:33:02,660 --> 00:33:03,800
Who was it?

512
00:33:05,530 --> 00:33:06,720
That's none of your business.

513
00:33:12,080 --> 00:33:14,570
Isn't it too cheap at 6,000 won?

514
00:33:15,170 --> 00:33:17,420
Are you selling comics in the department store now?

515
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:19,310
That's not true.

516
00:33:20,310 --> 00:33:21,010
Hey, hey.

517
00:33:22,530 --> 00:33:24,210
What is it about?

518
00:33:24,310 --> 00:33:26,650
Why did he come to us again?

519
00:33:26,750 --> 00:33:28,710
I know you're an important employee, but still.

520
00:33:28,810 --> 00:33:30,930
Not only did he pay the hospital bill

521
00:33:31,030 --> 00:33:33,790
and he still comes to visit at night. I think...

522
00:33:37,280 --> 00:33:39,780
The director isn't interested in you, is he?

523
00:33:43,630 --> 00:33:46,640
That's the funniest joke I've ever heard, Dad.

524
00:33:46,740 --> 00:33:49,250
Seriously, Dad. Are you blinded by fatherly love?

525
00:33:49,350 --> 00:33:51,150
What kind of man would like her?

526
00:33:51,750 --> 00:33:52,560
Hello, Baek Su Bin.

527
00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:55,260
He is young, tall and has a nice car.

528
00:33:55,360 --> 00:33:56,600
Why would he like her?

529
00:33:59,570 --> 00:34:00,460
- I mean... - God.

530
00:34:02,690 --> 00:34:04,070
Stop annoying.

531
00:34:04,570 --> 00:34:06,150
If you don't want to get hit in the head.

532
00:34:10,620 --> 00:34:11,470
Put down the glass.

533
00:34:12,970 --> 00:34:13,980
See?

534
00:34:14,680 --> 00:34:16,830
How could he care about her, Dad?

535
00:34:16,930 --> 00:34:17,500
Hello.

536
00:34:18,100 --> 00:34:20,320
Maybe he acts differently outside. Don't you think so?

537
00:34:21,850 --> 00:34:22,970
That doesn't make sense.

538
00:34:25,500 --> 00:34:27,440
The director has a meeting today.

539
00:34:27,540 --> 00:34:28,810
So I'll represent him.

540
00:34:30,420 --> 00:34:32,970
In the list of stores for the food department

541
00:34:33,370 --> 00:34:36,640
Happy Milk replaced Ganghan Farm.

542
00:34:37,240 --> 00:34:38,920
Did the sales team change it?

543
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:40,170
Yes.

544
00:34:40,270 --> 00:34:42,240
It would be impossible to cooperate with Ganghan Farm.

545
00:34:42,340 --> 00:34:43,450
So I changed it.

546
00:34:43,850 --> 00:34:45,340
It cannot be replaced.

547
00:34:45,640 --> 00:34:47,510
It is very popular nowadays.

548
00:34:47,610 --> 00:34:50,440
and does not cooperate with any department stores.

549
00:34:50,740 --> 00:34:53,380
We should have it to differentiate our food department.

550
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,830
Do you think I don't know?

551
00:34:55,430 --> 00:34:57,320
I tried to convince them.

552
00:34:57,920 --> 00:34:58,970
Even though we offered them 10 billion,

553
00:34:59,070 --> 00:35:00,910
they will not join the store.

554
00:35:01,110 --> 00:35:02,750
That's their company policy.

555
00:35:03,650 --> 00:35:04,670
Let's try to convince ourselves...

556
00:35:04,770 --> 00:35:06,240
It's easier said than done.

557
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:08,360
Do you think the sales team is doing nothing?

558
00:35:08,660 --> 00:35:10,270
They won't even negotiate.

559
00:35:10,370 --> 00:35:11,530
How do we convince them?

560
00:35:13,060 --> 00:35:15,180
If you want, try it, Team Leader Baek.

561
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:23,690
Happy Milk is also a competing brand.

562
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:26,720
I see.

563
00:35:27,220 --> 00:35:29,150
It is important to be realistic.

564
00:35:29,550 --> 00:35:32,480
I will report to the director regarding the list.

565
00:35:32,980 --> 00:35:34,130
Let's move on.

566
00:35:45,250 --> 00:35:46,040
GANGHAN FARM

567
00:35:46,140 --> 00:35:48,150
5 HOURS 34 MINUTES

568
00:35:50,140 --> 00:35:51,730
Are you considering going there?

569
00:35:52,230 --> 00:35:55,020
You never know. Tomorrow is the weekend.

570
00:35:56,020 --> 00:35:57,870
Okay. Good luck.

571
00:35:58,470 --> 00:35:58,960
Okay.

572
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:16,460
Bravo!

573
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:18,900
That was great.

574
00:36:20,340 --> 00:36:21,410
Good job.

575
00:36:34,750 --> 00:36:35,790
Thank you.

576
00:36:36,690 --> 00:36:37,880
Good job.

577
00:36:38,380 --> 00:36:40,510
I don't know why they love golf.

578
00:36:41,110 --> 00:36:43,250
I wouldn't have come if it weren't for the chairwoman.

579
00:36:43,350 --> 00:36:44,660
When I consider that...

580
00:36:46,660 --> 00:36:48,550
Congratulations on hitting one at bat.

581
00:36:49,250 --> 00:36:51,270
What can I say about that? I'm Ban Ju Yeon.

582
00:36:51,570 --> 00:36:53,010
I am good at everything.

583
00:36:55,450 --> 00:36:58,360
Why was Ganghan Farm removed from the list?

584
00:36:58,660 --> 00:37:00,550
The business team decided so.

585
00:37:00,650 --> 00:37:03,510
Ganghan Farm will not be added to the department store.

586
00:37:03,610 --> 00:37:06,630
That's why it would be important if they joined us.

587
00:37:06,730 --> 00:37:08,440
Tell them to convince them somehow.

588
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:09,810
There's still time.

589
00:37:10,110 --> 00:37:13,920
Team leader Baek went to convince them today.

590
00:37:14,420 --> 00:37:15,270
Same?

591
00:37:15,870 --> 00:37:17,630
Although the result is not guaranteed.

592
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:21,360
I guess it will be resolved soon.

593
00:38:20,500 --> 00:38:22,120
I'll take it to you.

594
00:38:22,420 --> 00:38:24,160
No, no. It's heavy.

595
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:26,470
I'm going all the way to the farm.

596
00:38:26,570 --> 00:38:28,600
I'll carry it for you because it's heavy.

597
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:32,740
You are a nice lady. Thank you.

598
00:38:33,140 --> 00:38:36,080
Why did you come this far alone?

599
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:39,700
I'm going to visit a farm. Ganghan Farm.

600
00:38:40,700 --> 00:38:43,320
I heard their ice cream is delicious.

601
00:38:43,420 --> 00:38:44,920
But they only sell it here.

602
00:38:45,020 --> 00:38:47,440
I wanted to taste it and see the farm.

603
00:38:47,540 --> 00:38:49,860
God. You must have a lot of free time.

604
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:52,930
Why did you come all this way for ice cream?

605
00:38:53,030 --> 00:38:54,320
I know.

606
00:38:54,620 --> 00:38:56,070
I wish they would join.

607
00:38:56,170 --> 00:38:58,850
to the store so people can taste it more easily.

608
00:38:59,350 --> 00:39:02,190
They say that delicious food tastes better when you share it.

609
00:39:07,780 --> 00:39:08,980
What's going on?

610
00:39:12,390 --> 00:39:13,390
Give it to me.

611
00:39:13,790 --> 00:39:15,260
Give it to me.

612
00:39:16,930 --> 00:39:18,720
You got me, Director An.

613
00:39:20,170 --> 00:39:21,530
DIRECTOR AN JAE SUK

614
00:39:27,300 --> 00:39:28,480
Which company are you from?

615
00:39:28,580 --> 00:39:30,600
KEO thank you Yongsung?

616
00:39:31,100 --> 00:39:33,680
I'm from Yongsung's strategy team.

617
00:39:33,780 --> 00:39:35,880
My name is Baek Su Jeong. Nice to meet you.

618
00:39:36,180 --> 00:39:37,830
You don't have to greet me.

619
00:39:37,930 --> 00:39:40,740
Do you think I should sell my product in Yongsung?

620
00:39:41,140 --> 00:39:44,690
What I hate most are greedy heirs.

621
00:39:44,790 --> 00:39:45,620
Heirs.

622
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:48,270
So you refuse...

623
00:40:11,540 --> 00:40:13,830
This way, Director An.

624
00:40:15,890 --> 00:40:17,050
What is it about?

625
00:40:18,750 --> 00:40:19,970
You don't act like a regular employee,

626
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:22,290
when I see your appearance.

627
00:40:22,890 --> 00:40:24,490
Of course not. I am a Yongsung student...

628
00:40:24,590 --> 00:40:26,110
He is my younger brother,

629
00:40:30,110 --> 00:40:32,050
which was sponsored by Yongsung.

630
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:34,360
This young handsome guy?

631
00:40:36,060 --> 00:40:38,540
You were misled by his clothes and car.

632
00:40:39,240 --> 00:40:40,820
He is a driver.

633
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:44,040
He doesn't own that car or that clothes.

634
00:40:44,640 --> 00:40:46,210
You said you were nearby.

635
00:40:46,310 --> 00:40:48,190
He came to see his sister.

636
00:40:49,090 --> 00:40:50,900
That's great, Director An.

637
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,760
We'll take you to the farm. Get in.

638
00:40:52,860 --> 00:40:54,650
No. Give it to me. Give it.

639
00:40:54,750 --> 00:40:55,930
NO...

640
00:40:56,030 --> 00:40:57,400
The bag is already there.

641
00:40:57,500 --> 00:40:59,090
Get in, Director An.

642
00:40:59,190 --> 00:41:00,770
Carefully. Carefully.

643
00:41:03,100 --> 00:41:05,000
What are you doing? Take us away.

644
00:41:11,160 --> 00:41:11,870
What the hell?

645
00:41:14,860 --> 00:41:16,600
Why did you come here?

646
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:19,090
Go away. I can handle it myself.

647
00:41:20,470 --> 00:41:22,220
Are you angry that I came?

648
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:26,010
Mrs. Ah hates rich heirs like you.

649
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:29,030
We'll see how well you can do it yourself.

650
00:41:30,230 --> 00:41:32,040
I've come to help you.

651
00:41:34,340 --> 00:41:36,550
Have you come to help me?

652
00:41:37,150 --> 00:41:39,650
You don't have to feel moved.

653
00:41:41,350 --> 00:41:43,680
Did you come because you doubted my abilities?

654
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:45,860
You didn't think I could do it myself?

655
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:47,370
You can do it.

656
00:41:47,670 --> 00:41:48,870
You will do a good job.

657
00:41:50,130 --> 00:41:50,770
But?

658
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:54,180
But it's hard to work alone.

659
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:56,510
It's also lonely.

660
00:42:00,110 --> 00:42:01,580
It's okay if you don't need me.

661
00:42:05,580 --> 00:42:07,750
Okay. Let's convince her together.

662
00:42:08,550 --> 00:42:10,100
But pretend you're my brother.

663
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:11,340
Don't let him find out that you are a rich heir.

664
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:12,970
Why a younger brother?

665
00:42:13,570 --> 00:42:14,850
What was I supposed to say?

666
00:42:14,950 --> 00:42:17,060
Friend sounds weird and boyfriend sounds even worse.

667
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:18,190
Why is that weird?

668
00:42:18,290 --> 00:42:19,290
It's weird.

669
00:42:19,390 --> 00:42:21,150
I'm obviously much older.

670
00:42:21,650 --> 00:42:23,190
The guy may be younger.

671
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:24,170
If that's the case,

672
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:26,450
Isn't it weirder that your boss is younger?

673
00:42:27,560 --> 00:42:30,880
Stop talking nonsense and look for Director An.

674
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:32,970
She went this way.

675
00:42:34,640 --> 00:42:36,260
Why does it still confuse me?

676
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:41,620
What nonsense?

677
00:43:09,970 --> 00:43:10,660
What is it about?

678
00:43:13,690 --> 00:43:14,340
Director An!

679
00:43:18,910 --> 00:43:20,190
Sweetheart.

680
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:23,590
Director An.

681
00:43:24,940 --> 00:43:25,860
What is this?

682
00:43:29,220 --> 00:43:30,380
Wait for us.

683
00:43:39,860 --> 00:43:41,270
It's not easy.

684
00:43:41,470 --> 00:43:42,490
Let's give up.

685
00:43:42,890 --> 00:43:45,250
He's making fools of us.

686
00:43:45,850 --> 00:43:46,450
NO.

687
00:43:47,750 --> 00:43:48,880
We are already crazy.

688
00:43:48,980 --> 00:43:50,960
Is he rejecting it because I'm a rich heir?

689
00:43:51,060 --> 00:43:53,080
Her business thinking is weak.

690
00:43:54,240 --> 00:43:55,040
One more...

691
00:43:56,690 --> 00:43:59,020
Let's try to convince her one more time, okay?

692
00:44:04,420 --> 00:44:05,630
This is our last attempt.

693
00:44:08,360 --> 00:44:08,940
Exactly.

694
00:44:11,580 --> 00:44:12,500
Director An.

695
00:44:12,900 --> 00:44:14,960
God, you scared me.

696
00:44:15,060 --> 00:44:18,200
Are you determined to give me a heart attack?

697
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:20,030
Get out of my sight.

698
00:44:20,830 --> 00:44:23,040
I can't do this, Director An.

699
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:25,910
I can't give up when I see the farm.

700
00:44:26,010 --> 00:44:28,780
I want a lot of people to know about your products.

701
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:30,330
I don't care.

702
00:44:30,430 --> 00:44:31,850
Leave. Leave immediately.

703
00:44:31,950 --> 00:44:34,310
I'm serious, Director An. Let's talk for a moment...

704
00:44:34,410 --> 00:44:36,840
I have nothing to tell you. Go away.

705
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:38,310
Get out of my sight.

706
00:44:38,410 --> 00:44:39,810
- Go away. - Let's talk...

707
00:44:39,910 --> 00:44:40,400
Hello!

708
00:44:45,370 --> 00:44:47,470
God, I can't believe it.

709
00:44:47,570 --> 00:44:50,810
They're putting on a show on my farm.

710
00:44:50,910 --> 00:44:52,590
So that's a show.

711
00:45:00,590 --> 00:45:02,130
It's not open yet.

712
00:45:04,800 --> 00:45:05,900
What brings you here?

713
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:07,330
I came to see you.

714
00:45:07,830 --> 00:45:10,780
- Behind me? - It's about...

715
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:12,770
I don't think I can separate them.

716
00:45:12,870 --> 00:45:15,660
We need a plan.

717
00:45:15,960 --> 00:45:17,760
You should have called first.

718
00:45:18,760 --> 00:45:21,160
I was just getting ready to go to the market.

719
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:25,100
Really? We can talk on the way, right?

720
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:25,800
Shall we go?

721
00:45:33,870 --> 00:45:37,250
You like internet novels.

722
00:45:37,350 --> 00:45:38,610
I knew it.

723
00:45:38,910 --> 00:45:41,480
I love your writing on Storygram.

724
00:45:41,580 --> 00:45:44,360
I read some novels even in the army.

725
00:45:44,460 --> 00:45:45,680
In the army?

726
00:45:45,780 --> 00:45:49,040
Yes. Everything is fun there except the training.

727
00:45:50,210 --> 00:45:51,710
Are you still playing?

728
00:45:52,110 --> 00:45:53,090
Sometimes.

729
00:45:54,090 --> 00:45:55,830
I used to play often before the restaurant opened.

730
00:45:55,930 --> 00:45:57,770
But I have a lot of work to do now.

731
00:45:58,270 --> 00:46:00,820
I also left the position of team leader to someone else.

732
00:46:01,320 --> 00:46:02,860
Why do you keep asking me questions about me?

733
00:46:03,060 --> 00:46:05,210
You came to talk about Ju Yeon and Su Jeong.

734
00:46:05,810 --> 00:46:08,060
Yes, he came.

735
00:46:08,160 --> 00:46:09,860
That's why I'm here.

736
00:46:10,460 --> 00:46:13,290
What are we going to do with those two?

737
00:46:14,090 --> 00:46:16,620
They ended up in the same company together.

738
00:46:17,220 --> 00:46:18,560
But I was relieved,

739
00:46:19,060 --> 00:46:20,860
that they don't meet on weekends.

740
00:46:21,660 --> 00:46:23,660
Really, don't you have any plans for the weekend?

741
00:46:24,060 --> 00:46:25,650
Do you mind if we're here?

742
00:46:25,750 --> 00:46:27,480
Many people want to meet you.

743
00:46:31,090 --> 00:46:31,890
GYU MYEONG

744
00:46:33,300 --> 00:46:34,830
I don't have a meeting with anyone. No.

745
00:46:51,310 --> 00:46:54,540
Do you always wear the same clothes?

746
00:46:55,240 --> 00:46:56,130
Of course.

747
00:46:56,530 --> 00:46:58,710
I came prepared. Better than anyone else.

748
00:46:59,840 --> 00:47:00,830
But this place is...

749
00:47:01,030 --> 00:47:03,680
You've changed. Why don't you sit down?

750
00:47:04,280 --> 00:47:07,540
Is this really your house, Director An?

751
00:47:08,040 --> 00:47:10,340
I'm worried about Ganghan Farm's finances.

752
00:47:10,440 --> 00:47:12,870
Why? What worries you?

753
00:47:13,770 --> 00:47:16,700
Hey, Ban Ju Yeon. Do you want to get spanked on the ass?

754
00:47:18,950 --> 00:47:21,380
- A spanking? - She donated all her property.

755
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:24,780
and led a humble life. You are impudent.

756
00:47:24,880 --> 00:47:25,960
Apologize.

757
00:47:27,450 --> 00:47:28,010
Cheeky?

758
00:47:30,930 --> 00:47:34,500
But shouldn't you live in a nicer house?

759
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:35,890
You worked hard.

760
00:47:35,990 --> 00:47:38,340
Why? What's wrong with my house?

761
00:47:38,440 --> 00:47:41,230
That's enough for me.

762
00:47:41,330 --> 00:47:42,980
Don't be foolish.

763
00:47:43,080 --> 00:47:45,050
Let's sit down and eat.

764
00:47:47,410 --> 00:47:49,130
Would you give me a spanking?

765
00:47:50,570 --> 00:47:52,170
It's my ass...

766
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:55,900
That's a lot of rice.

767
00:47:56,000 --> 00:47:57,480
It's not that much.

768
00:47:57,580 --> 00:47:59,510
That's why you're so skinny.

769
00:47:59,610 --> 00:48:01,200
Then add more.

770
00:48:02,100 --> 00:48:05,010
- Okay. - Try this too. It's godeulbbaegi.

771
00:48:05,110 --> 00:48:07,370
It's a little hot, but delicious.

772
00:48:07,470 --> 00:48:09,570
I picked it in the garden.

773
00:48:12,300 --> 00:48:13,040
Okay.

774
00:48:17,540 --> 00:48:19,270
What? You won't eat?

775
00:48:21,870 --> 00:48:22,540
Sister.

776
00:48:23,640 --> 00:48:26,970
What? Did you address me?

777
00:48:27,270 --> 00:48:29,810
It was collected by Director An.

778
00:48:29,910 --> 00:48:31,560
You won't refuse to eat it, will you?

779
00:48:31,660 --> 00:48:32,760
That would be rude.

780
00:48:36,130 --> 00:48:37,250
Of course not.

781
00:48:38,250 --> 00:48:39,180
Okay.

782
00:48:41,380 --> 00:48:43,240
Enjoy it, sister.

783
00:48:45,380 --> 00:48:48,570
Enjoy it too, brother.

784
00:48:48,670 --> 00:48:50,620
You love spicy foods.

785
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:53,920
Thank you, sister.

786
00:48:54,720 --> 00:48:56,450
You are so caring towards each other.

787
00:49:07,280 --> 00:49:10,650
Yes, yes. God, my baby.

788
00:49:10,750 --> 00:49:14,760
Yes. Of course I'm fine. I'm fine.

789
00:49:14,860 --> 00:49:16,130
Have you eaten?

790
00:49:18,110 --> 00:49:20,350
Okay, okay. Bye.

791
00:49:20,450 --> 00:49:22,950
Okay. We'll talk later.

792
00:49:29,450 --> 00:49:31,400
That must have been your grandson.

793
00:49:31,500 --> 00:49:31,920
Yes.

794
00:49:33,840 --> 00:49:36,720
He loves me very much.

795
00:49:37,520 --> 00:49:40,950
He just passed the bar exam and is working.

796
00:49:41,050 --> 00:49:43,280
He called me on the way home.

797
00:49:43,980 --> 00:49:46,260
I don't know who he is, but he's smart.

798
00:49:46,860 --> 00:49:48,390
He must look like you.

799
00:49:51,560 --> 00:49:52,480
Really?

800
00:49:53,580 --> 00:49:55,550
You must be proud of him.

801
00:49:55,950 --> 00:49:57,510
Any.

802
00:49:59,310 --> 00:50:03,090
He was born prematurely and was often sick.

803
00:50:03,290 --> 00:50:05,930
It was enough for me that he grew up healthy,

804
00:50:06,130 --> 00:50:08,230
but he is already an adult.

805
00:50:09,130 --> 00:50:14,100
People call me a wretch for living like this.

806
00:50:14,200 --> 00:50:16,470
They think I work just to give away money,

807
00:50:16,570 --> 00:50:18,250
but I don't do it without reason.

808
00:50:18,650 --> 00:50:22,110
A good world for children to live in.

809
00:50:22,410 --> 00:50:24,980
I wanted to create such a company.

810
00:50:25,080 --> 00:50:27,220
I don't want to be a rich grandma.

811
00:50:28,120 --> 00:50:31,040
I want to be a grandmother they are proud of.

812
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:36,480
Your grandson must be happy.

813
00:50:39,170 --> 00:50:41,320
His grandmother loves him so much.

814
00:50:45,340 --> 00:50:49,080
That's why you should work with Yongsung.

815
00:50:49,580 --> 00:50:52,220
God, you won't give up.

816
00:50:52,720 --> 00:50:55,020
I thought you were just an employee.

817
00:50:55,320 --> 00:50:57,610
How much do they actually pay you?

818
00:50:58,610 --> 00:51:00,120
That's not true.

819
00:51:00,720 --> 00:51:03,030
Another company will take your place.

820
00:51:03,430 --> 00:51:08,130
I want you to make a lot of money and not someone else.

821
00:51:08,630 --> 00:51:11,270
It would be nice if you became more influential.

822
00:51:11,570 --> 00:51:13,140
I also want to help you.

823
00:51:15,670 --> 00:51:17,790
That's tenacity. Seriously.

824
00:51:17,990 --> 00:51:20,470
Eat first. We'll talk later.

825
00:51:20,670 --> 00:51:22,830
If that's the impression, you'll listen to me, okay?

826
00:51:22,930 --> 00:51:23,500
Okay.

827
00:51:38,530 --> 00:51:40,240
Mix it up, bro.

828
00:51:56,180 --> 00:51:57,260
This is...

829
00:52:01,070 --> 00:52:03,300
Is this a new product you are working on?

830
00:52:03,400 --> 00:52:04,390
Can I try it?

831
00:52:04,490 --> 00:52:06,060
Yes, go ahead.

832
00:52:18,420 --> 00:52:19,300
What is this?

833
00:52:20,100 --> 00:52:21,240
Is that yogurt?

834
00:52:21,340 --> 00:52:23,280
It would be a huge success.

835
00:52:23,780 --> 00:52:24,810
Do you want to try?

836
00:52:26,740 --> 00:52:27,660
Tu.

837
00:52:28,960 --> 00:52:30,420
Drink it. Drink it.

838
00:52:31,020 --> 00:52:32,980
You're trying a new product from Ganghan Farm.

839
00:52:33,080 --> 00:52:34,760
You should be honored.

840
00:52:39,600 --> 00:52:41,700
- It's alcohol. - Yes.

841
00:52:41,830 --> 00:52:44,220
This is the makgeolli I made.

842
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:48,030
I used water from a spring in the mountain.

843
00:52:48,130 --> 00:52:49,060
It must be good.

844
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:53,480
How stupid.

845
00:52:55,660 --> 00:52:57,750
Stupid? You're being rude to me.

846
00:52:57,850 --> 00:52:58,890
Don't yell at me.

847
00:52:59,190 --> 00:53:01,400
How are you getting home, sister?

848
00:53:03,460 --> 00:53:06,510
I can go back by bus.

849
00:53:07,310 --> 00:53:09,190
You should have left already.

850
00:53:09,390 --> 00:53:10,800
The buses stopped running.

851
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:13,930
We'll call the driver.

852
00:53:15,390 --> 00:53:18,670
The driver? I thought you were the driver.

853
00:53:19,270 --> 00:53:21,620
That is, a driver service.

854
00:53:21,720 --> 00:53:24,250
Will you pay for the trip from here to Seoul?

855
00:53:26,010 --> 00:53:26,900
Can't I?

856
00:53:30,090 --> 00:53:33,440
God, your father runs a hardware store.

857
00:53:33,540 --> 00:53:37,150
and is paying off the debt due to your mother's illness.

858
00:53:37,250 --> 00:53:40,970
You mentioned that you are trying to pay off a loan.

859
00:53:41,070 --> 00:53:44,760
But your brother doesn't seem to be suffering too much.

860
00:53:46,840 --> 00:53:48,780
I thought you weren't listening.

861
00:53:51,570 --> 00:53:54,270
Because he's immature. That's how he is.

862
00:53:54,370 --> 00:53:56,090
He is five years younger than me.

863
00:53:56,190 --> 00:53:58,500
He's a kid compared to me.

864
00:53:59,300 --> 00:54:00,180
Kid?

865
00:54:01,180 --> 00:54:03,060
How much will a trip to Seoul cost?

866
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:05,020
Why don't you just throw the money away?

867
00:54:05,120 --> 00:54:06,430
What will you do?

868
00:54:07,030 --> 00:54:07,610
Sister.

869
00:54:10,350 --> 00:54:11,160
What are we going to do?

870
00:54:11,660 --> 00:54:13,420
What do you mean, what are you going to do?

871
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:15,030
You will sleep here.

872
00:54:27,940 --> 00:54:31,120
The potatoes are nicely baked, Director.

873
00:54:32,220 --> 00:54:33,680
Am I not a brother anymore?

874
00:54:34,280 --> 00:54:36,470
Why? Are you calling me "sister" again?

875
00:54:37,370 --> 00:54:39,890
You sounded so convincing that I almost believed you.

876
00:54:43,140 --> 00:54:45,520
I'm sorry this happened.

877
00:54:45,820 --> 00:54:47,160
You should have left.

878
00:54:49,700 --> 00:54:50,900
You call this an apology?

879
00:54:52,910 --> 00:54:55,430
It's sweet. You have to love it.

880
00:54:58,640 --> 00:55:01,340
Think of it as a vacation.

881
00:55:02,340 --> 00:55:04,860
The air is pleasant and the stars are beautiful.

882
00:55:12,480 --> 00:55:13,990
I was just saying that.

883
00:55:14,990 --> 00:55:17,470
But this is really a vacation.

884
00:55:19,560 --> 00:55:21,890
I didn't go to any this year because of work.

885
00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:25,210
Why on everything

886
00:55:26,510 --> 00:55:27,520
Are you working so hard?

887
00:55:31,350 --> 00:55:32,560
When I was little,

888
00:55:34,060 --> 00:55:36,490
I used to swing upside down on climbing frames.

889
00:55:36,790 --> 00:55:40,500
But a passerby said that girls shouldn't play so rough.

890
00:55:41,100 --> 00:55:43,700
It annoyed me even as a child.

891
00:55:44,100 --> 00:55:45,910
So I played even harder.

892
00:55:47,920 --> 00:55:49,370
At school one day I

893
00:55:49,570 --> 00:55:51,150
The teacher told me to give up.

894
00:55:51,250 --> 00:55:52,240
the position of class president.

895
00:55:52,440 --> 00:55:54,860
He claimed that I couldn't be her because my mother couldn't take care of me.

896
00:55:54,960 --> 00:55:56,370
That's nonsense.

897
00:55:56,770 --> 00:55:58,360
You would become her, not her.

898
00:55:58,460 --> 00:55:59,410
I know.

899
00:56:00,310 --> 00:56:02,920
People set boundaries for me.

900
00:56:03,000 --> 00:56:05,500
and they judged me. I hated it.

901
00:56:06,420 --> 00:56:10,410
So I worked even harder when they told me no.

902
00:56:10,710 --> 00:56:12,010
I was so determined.

903
00:56:13,820 --> 00:56:17,140
I wanted to show that I could do things.

904
00:56:17,540 --> 00:56:18,690
Do you know what that feels like?

905
00:56:22,170 --> 00:56:22,950
Yes.

906
00:56:24,050 --> 00:56:26,410
You don't need approval from others,

907
00:56:28,730 --> 00:56:30,670
but I think I have that kind of personality.

908
00:56:31,470 --> 00:56:33,500
I want to do everything well.

909
00:56:33,800 --> 00:56:36,160
and I cannot bear to be despised.

910
00:56:36,660 --> 00:56:37,800
I am like that.

911
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:50,560
Me too.

912
00:56:52,600 --> 00:56:54,230
I want to be recognized.

913
00:56:55,130 --> 00:56:56,620
and do a good job.

914
00:56:57,720 --> 00:57:00,040
I can't stand contempt.

915
00:57:05,960 --> 00:57:07,040
Why are you smiling?

916
00:57:10,430 --> 00:57:15,010
I was thinking about the fact that we are the same.

917
00:57:15,710 --> 00:57:17,590
It's ridiculous. It doesn't make sense.

918
00:57:21,750 --> 00:57:23,250
Why wouldn't that make sense?

919
00:57:24,150 --> 00:57:25,790
We have one more thing in common.

920
00:57:27,810 --> 00:57:28,770
Our first loves.

921
00:57:34,010 --> 00:57:38,030
I don't ever want to run into my love either.

922
00:57:39,950 --> 00:57:41,090
I thought,

923
00:57:42,930 --> 00:57:45,440
that he will accept me as I am.

924
00:57:47,640 --> 00:57:48,750
But it was terrible.

925
00:57:53,000 --> 00:57:55,540
We both have the worst first loves.

926
00:57:56,240 --> 00:57:57,150
Shall we have a toast?

927
00:58:00,780 --> 00:58:01,580
Cheers.

928
00:59:07,620 --> 00:59:08,480
HA JIN

929
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:10,900
Excuse me.

930
00:59:15,720 --> 00:59:16,940
Yes, friend.

931
00:59:17,640 --> 00:59:20,150
I'm on a business trip with the director in Gangwon.

932
00:59:21,350 --> 00:59:23,940
He's not a man. He's the same age as Su Bin.

933
00:59:24,040 --> 00:59:25,880
How can I consider him a man?

934
00:59:35,410 --> 00:59:36,300
But still.

935
00:59:36,600 --> 00:59:38,870
Didn't you get too close to the director?

936
00:59:39,170 --> 00:59:40,160
Shouldn't I?

937
00:59:40,560 --> 00:59:42,130
It's better than being the CEO Killer.

938
00:59:42,230 --> 00:59:46,330
I don't want you to learn the unpleasant truth.

939
00:59:47,030 --> 00:59:48,470
An unpleasant truth?

940
00:59:48,970 --> 00:59:52,180
You said he was a rich heir.

941
00:59:52,580 --> 00:59:54,070
What if he is corrupt?

942
00:59:54,170 --> 00:59:55,440
I know you can't stand it.

943
00:59:55,540 --> 00:59:57,530
This would become a serious problem.

944
00:59:58,530 --> 00:59:59,900
Nuts, Ha Jin?

945
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:02,040
Why are you suddenly worried?

946
01:00:02,740 --> 01:00:03,660
It doesn't matter.

947
01:00:03,960 --> 01:00:05,180
You definitely said,

948
01:00:05,280 --> 01:00:07,080
that you don't consider the director a man.

949
01:00:07,280 --> 01:00:07,860
What?

950
01:00:09,900 --> 01:00:10,820
Yes.

951
01:00:11,720 --> 01:00:13,290
Okay. Keep it up.

952
01:00:17,220 --> 01:00:18,430
What's his problem?

953
01:00:20,280 --> 01:00:21,280
That's strange.

954
01:00:42,600 --> 01:00:43,260
Are you sleeping?

955
01:00:46,000 --> 01:00:47,960
He always falls asleep when he gets drunk.

956
01:00:48,960 --> 01:00:51,170
Get some sleep, director.

957
01:00:51,770 --> 01:00:52,290
Okay?

958
01:00:53,890 --> 01:00:54,890
Director.

959
01:01:05,690 --> 01:01:06,940
It's annoying.

960
01:01:08,810 --> 01:01:11,550
I wanted to wake you up.

961
01:01:14,250 --> 01:01:15,900
Why do you despise me?

962
01:01:17,700 --> 01:01:18,770
When did I do that?

963
01:01:55,360 --> 01:01:56,020
Still...

964
01:02:04,520 --> 01:02:05,900
Don't you consider me a man?

965
01:03:07,160 --> 01:03:10,550
MY DEAREST NEMEZIS